_source.txt: Keeping a film as “family friendly” as possible also means that when the villain wants to cut someone’s throat (which she does twice) the camera moves off scene and only returns after the deed is done with only a thin line across the victim’s throat and no blood splatter or pooling. It’s an eye rolling incongruity.  It’s like being forced to eat the plant based alternative to a real cheeseburger.  Eric Adams will probably love it, (I know, only SOME of you will get that). Some of the action sequences are pretty good.  But they’re also a gyp.  One sequence is actually repeated twice.  Once in the very beginning of the movie to grab your attention and again later as a major sequence in the third act.
